       ii..ccccaa is an image processing program  that  takes  from  two  to  eight
       (raster)  band  files and a signature file, and outputs the same number
       of raster band files transformed to provide maximum separability of the
       categories  indicated  by  the  signatures.  This implementation of the
       canonical components transformation is based on the algorithm contained
       in  the  LAS  image  processing system. CCA is also known as "Canonical
       components transformation".


       Typically the user will use the _i_._c_l_a_s_s program to  collect  a  set  of
       signatures  and  then  pass those signatures along with the raster band
       files to _i_._c_c_a.  The raster band file names are specified on  the  com-
       mand  line  by  giving the group and subgroup that were used to collect
       the signatures.


       The output raster map names are built by appending a ".1",  ".2",  etc.
       to the output raster map name specified on the command line.

